      <h1>How Many Cups in a Quart? (Kitchen Conversion Guide)</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">The quick answer: there are <strong>4 cups in a quart</strong>. Whether you are scaling a recipe, substituting container sizes, or helping a child with a homework problem, this is one of the most fundamental kitchen conversions you will ever use. But the world of volume measurement goes much deeper — from the full gallon-to-teaspoon hierarchy to metric equivalents, dry vs. liquid differences, and practical tips for accurate measuring. This guide gives you every conversion table you need, explains the concepts behind the numbers, and helps you navigate measurement questions with confidence in any kitchen context.</p>
    </header>

